<test>
<name>No CCR-U should send although interface proxy restarted</name>
<qcid></qcid>
<description>
This test intend to validate that no CCR-U send if the interface proxy restarted and seconds GET request issued while in the time frame configured (pcrfValiditySecs) for PCRF.
</description>
<steps>
Write reqmod file to remote XTT
Load reqmod
Verify reqmod loaded
Restart the LOGGER
Start web server
Start diameter server
Radius login
Sleep for 5 secs
Compare string with the one return from the CER
Send GET request in order to issue CCR-I
Verify 200 OK
Extract from PSE
Query for the timestamp
Query for session name
Restart interface process
Send GET request while in the pcrf time frame
Verify 200 OK
Radius log off
Sleep for 5secs
Verify only 2 diameter requests sent
Get newest log file
Logscan it to x.log
Grep for CCR-U string in the transaction log
Verify that nothing received
Stop diameter server
Write empty reqmod to remote XTT
Load reqmod file
Verify reqmod loaded
Remove temporary file
Stop web server
</steps>
